UML:TaggedValue.value: RESQML profile. All non-date types are constrained to a maximum of 4000 characters and specialization (i.e., a new type) is disallowed. The xml:lang attribute is still allowed. Substitution groups have been eliminated which means for example that an "abstract" element cannot be substituted for a "description" element. That is, the element referenced in the RESQML schema is all that you will ever see in the XML. For dates, the attribute xsi:type="dct:W3CDTF" must be specified with each element with date content. This will constrain all dates to xs:dateTime. In the normative DC schema, W3CDTF represents a union of "xs:gYear xs:gYearMonth xs:date xs:dateTime". An xml:lang attribute is not allowed for dates.
